    "reasoning": "The design starts with core features and explicitly lists out-of-scope items (live streaming, ads, ML models). It describes system characteristics (high availability, read-heavy) but does not quantify SLAs (e.g., no latency target or availability percentage). Assumptions are stated in capacity planning, not in scoping section. This matches level 3: functional and non-functional stated, explicit assumptions, no quantified SLAs.",
